        "title": "How to inject a implementation that takes some value in its constructor in Guice?",
        "body": "<p>I have following implementation that I am trying to Inject in Guice<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>`public class Client{ \n   private final Database db; \n   public Client(Database db){ \n     this.db = db \n   } \n}\n\nclass SomeClass{ \n  private Client client; \n\n  @Inject \n  public SomeClass(Client client){ \n    this.client = client; \n  } \n}`\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>This is my injection code\nInjector guice = Guice.Injector();\nguice.getInstance(SomeClass.class);<\/p>\n\n<p>But I keep on getting the error:<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Could not find a suitable constructor in\n  hello.package.helloworld.Client. Classes must have either one (and\n  only one) constructor annotated with @Inject or a zero-argument\n  constructor that is not private<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>How do I Inject a class that already takes some parameter?<\/p>\n",
