        "last_activity_date": 1503043241,
        "creation_date": 1503043241,
        "body": "<p>The error text is quite explicit: you haven't used <code>@Inject<\/code> on the constructor of <code>Client<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<p>So the idea is to make it so:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Client{ \n  private final Database db; \n  @Inject\n  public Client(Database db){ \n    this.db = db \n  } \n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>And if you don't know your database, but want to create it, consider using Guice's <a href=\"https://github.com/google/guice/wiki/AssistedInject\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">assisted injection<\/a>, that creates factory for you.<\/p>\n",
